09/03/2004
TIRANA, Albania -- The head of the OSCE presence in Albania, Osmo Lipponen, said Monday (8 March) that the organisation is ready to assist authorities in drafting parliamentary regulations.
Lipponen met with Parliament Speaker Servet Pellumbi, who expressed gratitude for the OSCE support.
Pellumbi pledged his country's commitment to improve the legislative base and the work of state institutions.
In other news, Albania signed two co-operation agreements Monday with Bosnia and Herzegovina.
The accords envision bilateral co-operation in promoting tourism and air transport between the two countries.
Delegations also discussed co-operation in the fields of energy, transport, tourism, construction, education and culture.
(ATA, SRNA, HINA - 08/03/04)
